\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line PC Training and  Business College is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a higher education provider and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC.\line \line At the AC meeting of 27 July 2011\'2C the  institution was requested to provide clarity with regard to the application in the following areas\'3A\line 1. The institution must clarify or rectify the contradictory statements in the submission. As an example\'2C in the Programme Design Summary the course descriptors indicate the modules are on NQF level 5\'2C but elsewhere at Level 6\'2C and the module Advanced Business Management is described both as a 12 credit module and a 10-credit module.\line 2. The institution should ensure that the latest books including information with the latest developments in the field are prescribed. Reference is made to the prescribed textbook for Human Resource Management\'2C which is a 2003 edition\'2C lacking information on the latest legal and IR developments.\line \line Further information was submitted. \cell \pard 

