\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line As with other programmes submitted for accreditation from this institution the narrative does not sufficiently address distance education and the programme is not recommended for accreditation in the distance education mode of delivery. \line The evaluator indicated that\'2C based on the additional information provided\'2C Criterion 1 meets minimum standards. All modules are now correctly placed on NQF level 6 with a standard credit value of 10 credits per module. The programme still focuses on the functional areas of Management\'2C Human Resource Management and Business Law. The evaluator advised that the Institution review its mission statement in order to remove the focus from Financial Management\'2C Marketing and Entrepreneurship as there is very limited coverage of these functional areas in the Programme Design and it may therefore create false expectations among the learners. The list of prescribed textbooks has been successfully reviewed. The evaluator felt that there remains a concern regarding the duplication of textbooks from one programme to another.  For example\'2C the textbooks being prescribed in the Higher Certificate in Commerce overlap with the textbooks prescribed for the Advanced Certificate. \line Criteria 2\'2C 3\'2C 4\'2C 5\'2C 6\'2C 7 and 8 are judged as to be in need of improvement\'2C but these relate mainly to the distance education mode of delivery. Concerns raised by the evaluator include \line \'E2\'80\'A2 students\'27 English proficiency\'2C which was flagged as a concern by the institution\'2C but not addressed as part of the admissions and selection process. \line \'E2\'80\'A2 Some of the staff members have recently completed their own studies and are not sufficiently experienced to teach on the programme\line \'E2\'80\'A2 There is an inconsistency regarding the lecturer\'3Astudent ratio allocation across sites. \line The Directorate recommends that the programme should be accredited for the contact mode of delivery.  \line \cell \pard 

